com.codefactory.gwt.domiterator.client
Interface IElementMatcher

All Known Implementing Classes:
ClassnameRegexMatcher, IdRegexMatcher, MultiClassnameCaseInsensitiveMatcher, MultiClassnameCaseSensitiveMatcher, SingleClassnameCaseInsensitiveMatcher, SingleClassnameCaseSensitiveMatcher
public interface IElementMatcher

Interface used by the DomIterator. The DomIterator calls the matches(Element) method to check if the element matches the search criteria that this IElementMatcher implements. If matches(element) returns true, the element will be returned by the DomIterator. Can be used to check any attribute or property of an element. For example, a matcher could be defined to find all elements with a certain id or class name or background color.
